flatpak: flatpak (linux application sandboxing and distribution framework)
flatpak:
flatpak: Flatpak is a system for building, distributing, and running
flatpak: sandboxed desktop applications on Linux.
flatpak: Flatpak can be used by all kinds of desktop applications, and aims
flatpak: to be as agnostic as possible regarding how applications are built.
flatpak: While Flatpak only runs on Linux, it can be used by applications
flatpak: that target other operating systems, as well as those that are
flatpak: Linux-specific.
flatpak:
flatpak: See also: https://flatpak.org/
